      <h1 class="title is-2">Using search</h1>

        The search is using <code>key: value</code> pattern.<br/>
        For example, if your form has the following fields: <code>email, subject, body</code> and you want to find something you can type the following and hit search.<br/>
        <code>body: contact me</code> or search by email <code>email: user@example.com</code>. Same works for other fields that you might have.


      <figure>
        <img src="../images/search.png"/>

        <figcaption>
          Searching using body key
        </figcaption>
      </figure>

      <h1 class="title is-2">Some Api</h1>

      With the existing api you can fetch your mailboxes and messages.<br/>

      Make a post request to <code>formiqo.com/auth</code> with the following body
      <code>{"auth": {"email": "your_email", "password": "you_password"}}</code><br/>

      If the credentials are correct, you'll get a response with your jwt token <code>"jwt": "token"</code><br/>

      Now you can fetch a list of your mailboxes or a specific mailbox with:<br/>

      <ul>
        <li>GET <code>formiqo.com/api/mailboxes</code> - returns a list of all mailboxes</li>
        <li>GET <code>formiqo.com/api/mailboxes/c7536b6acd26bd47</code> - returns a mailbox with nested messages</li>
      </ul>

      Don't forget to set the following headers:
        <code>Content-Type: application/json </code>,
        <code>Authorization: your_jwt_token </code>


